article.description: Oren Milstein kicked three field goals and Columbia beat Dartmouth 9-7 on Saturday to snap a seven-game losing streak to the Big Green, dating to 2008.
article.headline: Milstein kicks 3 FGs to help Columbia beat Dartmouth 9-7
article.linkText: Milstein kicks 3 FGs to help Columbia beat Dartmouth 9-7
article.story: NEW YORK -- Oren Milstein kicked three field goals and Columbia beat Dartmouth 9-7 on Saturday to snap a seven-game losing streak to the Big Green, dating to 2009. Milstein, a freshman who earlier this season set a school record for field goals in a game with five, was good from 31, 20, and 33 yards -- but missed on a 38-yard attempt in the fourth quarter. He's hit on 9 of 10 attempts this season. Alan Watson rushed for 74 yards on 17 carries for the Lions (2-4, 1-2 Ivy). Anders Hill completed 12 of 25 passes for 123 yards. Dartmouth (3-3, 0-3) was led by Jack Heneghan, who completed 13 of 38 for 242 yards with a 65-yard touchdown pass to Hunter Hagdorn. Hagdorn had three catches for 114 yards. David Smith missed a 47-yard field goal with 21 seconds to go.
